edu.umaryland.igs.idea
Class SummaryTableModel

java.lang.Object
  javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel
      edu.umaryland.igs.idea.SummaryTableModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, TableModel
Direct Known Subclasses:
PairwiseSummaryTableModel, StandardSummaryTableModel
public abstract class SummaryTableModel
extends AbstractTableModel

SummaryTableModel represents the back end for the table displayed by IDEAOutputGUI. Its contents are derived from the .mlc files created by IDEA or potentially from PAML output files not generated by IDEA. The data are stored in a complex data structure described below. SummaryTableModel is an abstract class. It is extended by the concrete classes StandardSummaryTableModel and PairwiseSummaryTableModel.

load

public static SummaryTableModel load(String dirName,
                                     JFrame owner,
                                     edu.umaryland.igs.aegan.utils.SwingThreadSafeComponent<JProgressBar> progress)
                              throws IOException
The static method load creates a SummaryTableModel from data in files in the specified directory. This method follows the factory object pattern: It returns an instance of a concrete subclass.

Parameters:
dirName - the directory containing the .mlc files to use
owner - the GUI into which results are being loaded
progress - a progress bar to update as loading progesses; may be null
Throws:
IOException - if an output file is deleted while data is being loaded or an I/O error occurs

public abstract LinkedList<String> buttons(int column)
The buttons method returns a linked list containing the string names of the buttons that should be displayed in the specified column's header. The column names are associated with the names of methods to be activated when the buttons are clicked. See class SummaryTableButton.

Parameters:
column - the index of the column whose button names are to be listed
Returns:
a linked list of the names of the buttons that should be displayed in the specified column's header

leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected

public abstract int leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected()
Row selection is indicated on the table by displaying an outline around all or some of the row's cells. The leftMostColumnToDisplayAsSelected method returns the index of the leftmost column to be included in the outlined area when a row is selected.

Returns:
the leftmost column to be included in the outlined area when a row is selected

numericalValuesInColumn

public abstract LinkedList<Double> numericalValuesInColumn(int column,
                                                           String model)
The numericalValuesInColumn method returns a linked list of the values in the requested column (which should be a numeric column). This is useful for making histograms. Only values in rows matching the given model are included in the returned list.

Parameters:
column - the requested column
model - the model to restrict results to, or StandardSummaryTableModel.LIKELIEST
Returns:
a linked list of values for the requested model in the requested column

nextBackgroundColor

protected Color nextBackgroundColor()
The nextBackgroundColor method is used to alternate the background colors for datasets in the table. It returns whichever of the two row background colors was not returned the last time it was called.

Returns:
the row background color that was not returned the last time nextBackgroundColor

assignColorTo

void assignColorTo(Object datasetIdentifier)
The assignColorTo method associates the next background color with the specified dataset unless that dataset is already associated with a background color. The association lasts until the table is re-sorted.

Parameters:
datasetIdentifier - the dataset (probably a String) with which to associate the next background color

getColor

Color getColor(Object datasetIdentifier)
The getColor method returns the cell background color currently associated with the specified dataset.

Parameters:
datasetIdentifier - the dataset whose background color is being queried (probably a String)
Returns:
the cell background color currently associated with datasetIdentifier

resetColors

protected void resetColors()
The protected method resetColors is called by sortAscendingGlobal and sortDescendingGlobal. It removes all dataset-color associations so the sorted table will still have alternating colors, one for each dataset.

sortAscendingGlobal

public void sortAscendingGlobal(int columnIndex,
                                JFrame ownerWindow)
The sortAscendingGlobal method sorts across datasets in ascending order of the specified parameter. Numeric values appear in ascending order above string values, which appear in ascending order above non-numeric, non-string values. This method modifies the underlying data structure. NOTE: This is a button method. See class SummaryTableButton.

Parameters:
columnIndex - the index of the column on which to sort
ownerWindow - ignored; may be null (This parameter exists for all button methods since some may require it.)

sortDescendingGlobal

public void sortDescendingGlobal(int columnIndex,
                                 JFrame ownerWindow)
The sortDescendingGlobal method sorts across datasets in descending order of the specified parameter. Numeric values appear in descending order above string values, which appear in descending order above non-numeric, non-string values. This method modifies the underlying data structure. NOTE: This is a button method. See class SummaryTableButton.

Parameters:
columnIndex - the index of the column on which to sort
ownerWindow - ignored; may be null (This parameter exists for all button methods since some may require it.)
